<seg id=1> A Colorful Fine-Grained Pebble "China-Pebble with 5 Uniquenesses" Makes Debut </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency. Nanjing. Sept. 1. (Reporter Yuan Yanghe) Professor Liu Yuyi, whose famous oil painting "Pleasant Night" has ever caused a sensation in the world of paintings, the other day in Nanjing made public a pebble named "China-Pebble with 5 Uniquenesses" he found. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> This colorful pebble in shape and size is extremely like the folk mascot long-life lock. </seg>
<seg id=4> In the very center of the colorful pebble is a rather distinct image of the territory of the People's Republic of China. </seg>
<seg id=5> The two ends of the image stand tall, the middle dented, the right bottom protruded. It is just like a chest-and-belly-protruding, neck-craned singing cock. At the belly side of the "cock", across a "strip of strait", is a long and narrow "Taiwan Island". Under the claws of the "cock" is the round "Hainan Island". </seg>
<seg id=6> The color of the two "islands" is completely the same with that of the "mainland". </seg>
<seg id=7> The entire image is extremely like the map of China. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Professor Liu Yuyi said, this colorful pebble was picked up by him five years ago on a road of a colorful pebble processing factory in a suburb of Nanjing. After getting home and studying it closely, he found "the territory of China" on it. </seg>
<seg id=9> Meanwhile, he also found, on the top of the territory of the mainland, along the border line from the Northeast through North China to the Northwest, winds a titanic dragon with a bright pearl in its mouth; above the titanic dragon is a golden gold-ingot-shaped facula; in the middle of the territory of China are a bunch of torch-shaped stripes, symbolizing the never-dying life fire of the Chinese people; plus that the pubble in shape is like a long-life lock, altogether it has five characteristics. </seg>
<seg id=10> Liu Yuyi, according to these, named the pebble " China-Pebble with 5 Uniquenesses" </seg>
</p>
